        "text": "BBC show Father Brown is in its ninth series and the plot has constantly kept viewers guessing.\n\nIt has seen many famous faces in the cast throughout the years, but a true stalwart of the series is English actor John Light.\n\nJohn is best known for playing the role of Hercule Flambeau and has done it consistently since the show aired.\n\nREAD MORE: The Father Brown star's appearance in The Bill, marriage to ITV Endeavour star and siblings who starred in Coronation Street and Heartbeat\n\nThe long-running series, which originally aired in 2013, was even filmed partly in the heart of Oxford.\n\nOne face to join the series is British actor John Light who plays the role Hercule Flambeau.\n\nMany fans probably recognise John as the ultimate nemesis of Father Brown but there's much more to meet the eye, including a brief four-year ex-marriage to a major Hollywood star.\n\nJohn has appeared alongside several famous faces in the series, including Sorcha Cusack, Nancy Carroll, Mark Williams and Emer Kenny, just to name a few.\n\nWho is John Light?\n\nJohn is born on 30 September 1973.\n\nThe 49-year-old was born in Birmingham.\n\nHe is an English television, theatre and film actor who even received a Laurence Olivier Award nomination for his supporting role in the play Taken at Midnight.\n\nIn 1998, John played his first on-screen role in Cider with Rosie.\n\nHe later continued appearances in several series and films on-screen throughout the years including, The Lion in Winter, A New World: A Life of Thomas Paine, Silk and WPC 56, just to name a few.\n\nIn 2013. he first appeared as the nemesis of Father Brown in the BBC show as character Hercule, and still plays the role presently.\n\nSince 2013, he has also appeared in Lewis, Maigret, Taken at Midnight, Mary Stuart, Florian Zeller, Uncle Vanya and more.\n\nWhat is John Light's net worth?\n\nJohn has a net worth of around $3 million.\n\nThis is the equivalent of over £2.5 million.\n\nWho is John Light's ex-wife?\n\nJohn married Neve Campbell in 2007 and underwent a brief marriage until they divorced in 2011.\n\nThe couple originally met while filming Investigating Sex.\n\nShe is a Canadian actress who has dedicated her work to specialising in drama and horror genres.\n\nNeve even featured in the People magazine's list of 50 Most Beautiful People twice.\n\nShe has a glittering portfolio in major holiday movies at just 48-years-old, but she is probably known best as the Scream Queen for appearing in the horror franchise.\n\nShe appeared in the films alongside David Arquette and Courteney Cox, best known for playing Monica on Friends.\n\nNeve has also worked alongside major Hollywood actors in films including the Scream franchise, The Lion King 2: Simba's Pride, Wild Things, The Craft, and Three to Tango, just to name a few.\n\nShe has even worked alongside Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson in Skyscraper."
